name="doi">10.48550/arXiv.2305.01474</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We study the 2-category theory of Grothendieck fibrations in the 2-category of functors <fr:tex>\mathbf {Cat} ^{ \to }</fr:tex>. After redrawing a few general results in that context, we show that fibrations over a given base are pseudo-coalgebras for a 2-comonad on  <fr:tex>{ \mathbf {Cat} } _{ / B }</fr:tex>. We use that result to explain how an arbitrary fibration is equivalent to one with a splitting.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>